@Kami Nana
He was never just friends with her. His whole behaviour was centered around staying close to her until he gathers up courage to confess. So him believing that he can just go back to how it was is a bit silly. That's not moving on, even though he tries to.
Same with Chitose obviously. Although her main flaw seems to be a need to project an image of purity. Maybe for his sake, maybe for her own.

@dragonnina642
Yes, lack of confidence is a serious hurdle in life, including relationships. But you weren't making an observation, you were making a judgement. 'He is to blame for his situation' is different than 'his personality led to this situation'. That is what I'm adressing first and foremost.
As for Taka, irl what he did to Chitose in the classroom would amount to rape. Obviously this is porn logic so who cares. No Taka's not a psychopath like most ntr bulls are. But he's not the most pleasant person either.

@pettam2.0 No new chapter as yet. Probably be a while since it'll be upwards of 30 pages. I hope it's out in 2 months, 4 months feels so long haha. 
@camilakilla Thanks, I'm just trying to chat and discuss with folks a piece of media I'm really enjoying. XD
@azembo Triangle Café feels a more comedic piece in comparison. The characters' motivations and the manner in which they accomplish them are bizarre. Like the sex play with Kurono was an attempt to make Oohashi confess while Kurono himself had a little fun. It failed spectacularly which I thought was funny. I think it's meant to be approached more whimsically. I get what you mean about Tamaki's behaviour being rather odd but I never really took her actions seriously you know? Her actions seem way too out there lol.

